Day 5 – Consolidated OOP Assignment
Topics Covered: Classes & Objects · Member Variables & Methods · __init__ · Private
Members · Static Members · Operator Overloading · Inheritance · Custom Exception Classes
Instructor: Vinod

Assignment Title
Employee Payroll & Management System (OOP-Based Design)

Problem Statement

We are building an internal Employee Payroll and Management System for his Bangalore-
based training and consulting firm.

You are required to design and implement this system using Object-Oriented Programming
principles in Python.
The solution must be modular, clean, and must demonstrate correct use of OOP features
covered in Day 5.

Core Requirements

1. Base Class – Person

Create a class Person that represents a generic person.
Attributes
name (public)
city (public)
Methods

def __init__(self, name: str, city: str):
pass

